# Task 1 - Creating a Secure File

## Problem Statement

Create a confidential file to store sensitive project keys.

The file should only be accessible by its owner.

---

## Commands Used

```bash id="doqq7y"
touch project_keys.txt
chmod 600 project_keys.txt
```

---

## Solution

```bash id="ikdpsp"
cd ~/project/phoenix_project

touch project_keys.txt

chmod 600 project_keys.txt

ls -l
```

---

## Output

```bash id="vgkkjt"
-rw------- 1 labex labex 0 May 25 12:05 project_keys.txt
```

---

## Explanation

Permission `600` means:

| Permission | Value        |
| ---------- | ------------ |
| Owner      | Read + Write |
| Group      | No Access    |
| Others     | No Access    |

This ensures that sensitive project files remain protected from unauthorized users.

