# Task 2 - Ownership Management

## Problem Statement

Transfer ownership of the project resources to the development lead and developers group.

---

## Commands Used

```bash id="7i8krx"
sudo chown -R dev_lead:developers ~/project/phoenix_project
```

---

## Solution

```bash id="qgk4wa"
sudo chown -R dev_lead:developers ~/project/phoenix_project

ls -ld ~/project/phoenix_project
```

---

## Output

```bash id="j1ub4m"
drwxrwxr-x 4 dev_lead developers 53 May 25 12:05 phoenix_project
```

---

## Explanation

The `-R` flag applies ownership changes recursively to:

* files
* directories
* subdirectories

This is commonly used in production Linux environments while provisioning application infrastructure.

