# Task 4 - Configuring setgid Permissions

## Objective

Ensure all newly created files inherit the developers group automatically.

---

## Commands Used

```bash id="xez1lc"
sudo chmod 2770 ~/project/phoenix_project/src
```

---

## Output

```bash id="bxxy7v"
drwxrws--- 2 dev_lead developers 26 May 25 12:43 src
```

---

## Explanation

The leading `2` in `2770` enables the setgid bit.

Benefits:

* automatic group inheritance
* improved team collaboration
* consistent permission structure
* better operational management

This is widely used in:

* DevOps environments
* shared repositories
* deployment directories
* collaborative infrastructure setups

